<item>
            <title>[SPARK-23997] Configurable max number of buckets</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23997</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When exporting data as a table the user can&#160;choose to split data&#160;in buckets&#160;by choosing the&#160;columns and the number of buckets. Currently there is a hard-coded limit of 99&apos;999 buckets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, for heavy workloads this limit might be too restrictive, a situation that will eventually become more common as workloads grow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per the comments in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-19618&quot; title=&quot;Inconsistency wrt max. buckets allowed from Dataframe API vs SQL&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-19618&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-19618&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;this limit could be made configurable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
